#. lang="pi"><section class="sutta" id="thag1.1"><article><div
#. class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "thag1.1:1.1"
msgid "Theragāthā"
msgstr "Verses of the Senior Monks"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "thag1.1:2.1"
msgid "Ekakanipāta"
msgstr "The Book of the Ones"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "thag1.1:3.1"
msgid "Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "Chapter One"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "thag1.1:4.1"
msgid "1.1. Subhūtittheragāthā"
msgstr "1.1. Subhūti"

# HERE IS A COMMENT
#. </h1></div><h4 class="extra">
msgctxt "thag1.1:5.1"
msgid "Nidānagāthā"
msgstr "Background"

#. </h4><p class="namo">
msgctxt "thag1.1:6.1"
msgid "Namo tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts1"></a>
msgctxt "thag1.1:7.1"
msgid "Sīhānaṃva nadantānaṃ,"
msgstr "Like the lions of mighty fang"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:7.2"
msgid "dāṭhīnaṃ girigabbhare;"
msgstr "who roar in mountain caves—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:7.3"
msgid "Suṇātha bhāvitattānaṃ,"
msgstr "hear now from those who’ve practised well"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:7.4"
msgid ""
"gāthā <span class=\"var\" title=\"attupanāyikā (bj, pts1-2, mr) | "
"atthupanāyikā (s2, s3)\" id=\"note1\">atthūpanāyikā</span>."
msgstr "their own verses about themselves."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a>
msgctxt "thag1.1:8.1"
msgid "Yathānāmā yathāgottā,"
msgstr "What their name, and what their clan,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:8.2"
msgid "yathādhammavihārino;"
msgstr "and how they lived by the teaching;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:8.3"
msgid "Yathādhimuttā sappaññā,"
msgstr "how dedicated were those wise ones,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:8.4"
msgid "vihariṃsu atanditā."
msgstr "as they meditated tirelessly."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a>
msgctxt "thag1.1:9.1"
msgid "Tattha tattha vipassitvā,"
msgstr "Clearly seeing in every case,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:9.2"
msgid "phusitvā accutaṃ padaṃ;"
msgstr "they reached the imperishable state."

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:9.3"
msgid "Katantaṃ paccavekkhantā,"
msgstr "Reviewing their completed task,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:9.4"
msgid "imamatthamabhāsisuṃ."
msgstr "they spoke about it in these words."

#. </p></blockquote><h4>
msgctxt "thag1.1:10.1"
msgid "Subhūtittheragāthā"
msgstr "Subhūti"

#. </h4><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a
#. class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc1"></a><a class="verse-num-pts"
#. id="verse-num-pts1"></a>
msgctxt "thag1.1:11.1"
msgid "“Channā me kuṭikā sukhā nivātā,"
msgstr "My little hut is ro­ofed and pleasant, sheltered from the wind:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:11.2"
msgid "Vassa deva yathāsukhaṃ;"
msgstr "so rain, sky, as you please!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:11.3"
msgid "Cittaṃ me susamāhitaṃ vimuttaṃ,"
msgstr "My mind is serene and freed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.1:11.4"
msgid "Ātāpī viharāmi vassa devā”ti."
msgstr "I practice whole-heartedly: so rain, sky!"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "thag1.1:12.1"
msgid ""
"<span class=\"var\" title=\"itthaṃ sumaṃ (Ma-aka)\" id=\"note2\">Itthaṃ "
"sudaṃ</span> āyasmā subhūtitthero gāthaṃ abhāsitthāti."
msgstr ""
"It was thus that this verse was recited by the senior venerable Subhūti."
